neureka.backend.api

Class ExecutionCall<D extends Device<?>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • neureka.backend.api.Call<D>
      • neureka.backend.api.ExecutionCall<D>
  • Type Parameters:
    D - The Device implementation targeted by an instance of this ExecutionCall!

    public class ExecutionCall<D extends Device<?>>
extends Call<D>
    This class is a simple container holding references to a targeted Device, Operation and maybe some case specific meta Args needed to execute an array of input tensors which are also wrapped by this.

    This class is technically immutable, however the contents of the input array may be modified in order to calculate a suitable output. The meta arguments wrapped by this are responsible for storing operation specific variables like for example an input index for calculating a partial derivative. Certain operations might require other unique types of arguments...
